Reinforcement Learning, Theory.

Reinforcement Learning is the primary sub-category of AI that this paper belongs to. The paper discusses TD() learning, which is a type of reinforcement learning algorithm. The paper explores the generalization capabilities of TD() learning, which is a key aspect of reinforcement learning.

Theory is another sub-category of AI that this paper belongs to. The paper presents a theoretical analysis of TD() learning and its generalization capabilities. The authors derive bounds on the generalization error of TD() learning and provide insights into the conditions under which TD() learning can generalize well.
